com.flowpowered.commons

Class StringToUniqueIntegerMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.flowpowered.commons.store.SimpleStoredMap<Integer>
      • com.flowpowered.commons.StringToUniqueIntegerMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Named, StoredMap<Integer>

    public class StringToUniqueIntegerMap
extends SimpleStoredMap<Integer>
    Represents a map for mapping Strings to unique ids. The class supports conversion of ids between maps and allocation of new unique ids for unknown Strings Conversions to and from parent/child maps are cached

      • register

        public int register(String key)
        Registers a key with the map and returns the matching id. The id corresponding to a key will be consistent if registered more than once, including over restarts, subject to the persistence of the store.
        Parameters:
        key - the key to be added
        Returns:
        returns the local id, or 0 on failure

      • register

        public boolean register(String key,
                        int id)
        Registers a key/id pair with the map. If the id is already in use the method will fail.

        The id must be lower than the min id for the map to prevent clashing with the dynamically allocated ids
        Parameters:
        key - the key to be added
        id - the desired id to be matched to the key
        Returns:
        true if the key/id pair was successfully registered
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the id >= minId
